Introduction:

This documentation describes the input/output of the four http methods.
  • Making a get request
  • Making a put request with encding chracters
  • Making a delete request
  • Making a post request
  • Making an upload post request

Making a get request (top)

Request
  • HTTP: GET
  • URI: /resource/id:12345
Response
  • ResponseCode: 230
  • payload:
    {
  "abc": "123"
}
The response contains the HTTP_STATUS of the request
The response contains a JSON payload

Making a put request with encding chracters (top)

Request
  • HTTP: PUT
  • URI: /resource/id:12345
Response
  • ResponseCode: 230
  • payload:
    {
  "abc": "123"
}
The response contains the HTTP_STATUS of the request
The response contains a JSON payload

Request

  • payload:

  "abc": "123"

The response contains a JSON payload
